r’s domestic market by exploiting a wider global selection of inflationlinked bonds and currencies the fund will be split approximately  developed and  emerging markets ilb aims to deliver a more diversified inflation protection strategy importantly ilb will also be actively managed against a gross domestic product gdpweighted benchmark with the intent to better align investors’ exposure to countries experiencing stronger growth this is in contrast to traditional marketcap weighted benchmarks which allocate relative to the inflationlinked bond issuance of each country “in this uncertain global economy some of the key drivers of growth are developing economies which are often more sensitive to inflationary pressures like commodity prices” said worah “our forwardlooking ‘global advantage’ approach aims to expose investors to the inflationlinked bonds and currencies of these fastergrowing economies potentially resulting in higher real yields than traditional investing using market capweighting” pimco is one of the world’s largest managers of inflationlinked bonds and manages more than  billion in dedicated inflation hedging strategies the fund will list on  may  ilb follows the recent launch of the actively managed pimco total return etf bond which launched on  march  and has already gathered over m in aumyou may also be interested inpimco swaps management team on flagship active bond etfpimco unveils actively managed foreign currency strategy etfpimco total return etf officially goes livethe name’s bond pimco changes total return etf tickerpimco working on plans to launch further active etfspimco launches emerging markets advantage local bond index source etfvanguard unveils shortterm tips etf vtippimco and source unveil actively managed covered bond etfssga’s international government inflationlinked bond etf adopts citi indexpimco launches australia bond index etf canada and germany to followpimco total return etf date set for hotly awaited launchssga spdr unveils world’s first emerging markets inflationlinked bond etfpimco source add gbp trading line to em local bond etfbill gross’s pimco total return etf trxt set to be ‘bellwether’ active etfpimco bonds are different – the active advantage tags etf industry news global leave a comment click here to cancel reply name required email address will not be published required website notify me of followup comments by email notify me of new posts by email more from this category ig picks six of the best government bond etfs lyxor rolls out three fixed income etfs on borsa italiana blackrock slashes fees on ishares mbs etf blackrock launches cheapest floating rate bond etf in europe inspire investing unveils first faithbased bond etf lyxor launches short term high yield bond etf on lse vaneck your emerging markets bonds allocation may now be “junk” vaneck crosslists em bond on six guggenheim changes name of actively managed bn enhanced short duration etf citi expands wgbi and onshore china bond index suites browse by category alternatives  multiasset commodities equities etf and index news fixed income ftse russell – ifa video series latest news browse archives select month july  june  may  april  march  february  january  december  november  october  september  august  july  june  may  april  march  february  january  december  november  october  september  august  july  june  may  march  february  january  december  november  october  september  august  july  june  may  april  march  february  january  december  november  october  september  august  july  june  may  april  march  february  january  december  november  october  september  august  july  june  may  april  march  february  january  december  november  october  september    etf strategy ltd  disclaimer  cookies go to top more in fixed incomeishares launches morningstar  emerging markets corporate bond etf emcpishares has announced the launch of the first etf in europe to provide access to emerging market corporate bonds 